<br>
All around you, you see people holding torches, mostly people all in brown or gray cloaks discussing amongst them selves. You are quite not sure what’s going on, but you stay and see what all the commotion is about. <br>
<br>
Rain is pouring off your cloak, as you hear thunder off in the near distance. Several flashes of lighting light of the night sky… <br>
<br>
suddenly you see a man walk out of a bridge way, and onto the main catwalk of a castle wall, overlooking the crowd and a small in-castle village. <br>
<br>
With him he has a giant maul that is pulsating electricity, wearing a white cloak with golden emblems of a cross and a two handed claymore, with a shield. You are not sure, but you think he’s a paladin. You cannot see his face, for the hood of the cloak is forming a shadow…<br>
<br>
The crowd then became silent.. The man begins to speak in a loud, crisp voice with swift judgment. <br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;The ages have come.. Too many evils roam the land of Norrath… Too many… streets, and forests, alike…&quot; <br>
<br>
 “Too long have the evils roamed about in the daylight bathing in their own filth… This is a call, call to those whom are sick of the scum and over population of evils… Even our own brothers and sisters are being corrupt…” Thunder crackles as lighting again brightens the night sky.. <br>
<br>
The man then lifts of the hood of his cloak, and a masculine face, with gold long blonde hair, and clean shaved face, with goldish – silverish eyes.<br>
<br>
 “Intermarriages, with evil backwash… Sickening… theirs ways will end.. One week and 5 days we shall march across Norrath spilling the blood of the evils… Their time is up…”<br>
<br>
&quot;NOW! WHOS WITH ME….!?&quot; <br>
<br>
There was a great silence.. The rain was still pouring, it was silence for a good 2 minutes… a young warrior stood up, she seemed to be kneeling. <br>
<br>
”The evils of Norrath have slaughtered my kin and  tortured  my friends.. My sword and strength is one with you, mighty paladin.” <br>
<br>
As you look around you see one by one, the people their offer their skills, blood and lifes. Some sneered in sheer disgust and walked away… <br>
<br>
You feel mixed... Your not sure if you should join... go home or what.. <br>
<br>
You then feel a rush of emotion, you then yell out to the and paladin tell him what you have to say...  <br>
